# Applies to the repo-root build context shared by the Python service images
# (apps/api-python, apps/ingest-python) AND the React dashboard image
# (apps/dashboard-react/Dockerfile). The Kotlin image builds from its own scoped
# context (apps/ot-gateway-kotlin) and is unaffected.
#   Python images keep: packages/contracts/codegen/python + apps/*-python/{pyproject.toml,src}.
#   Dashboard image keeps: pnpm-lock.yaml, pnpm-workspace.yaml, root package.json,
#     apps/dashboard-react/{package.json,src,index.html,vite.config.ts,tsconfig.json,
#     *.config.*,public}, and packages/contracts/codegen/typescript (the @sdf/contracts
#     workspace dep the Vite build compiles in).
# The excludes below (node_modules / build / tests / .git / docs / .claude / secrets)
# are correct and beneficial for the dashboard too: the dashboard build emits to
# dist/ (not build/), reinstalls node_modules from the lockfile, and needs none of
# tests/, so nothing it requires is stripped.
.git
.github
.claude
docs
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/node_modules
**/build
**/.gradle
# Secret material must never enter the repo-root build context.
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/.aws
# Kotlin sources are not part of the Python images.
apps/ot-gateway-kotlin
# Tests are not copied into the runtime images.
**/tests
